content:
The username enumeration attack using rockyou.txt took too long and was manually interrupted. Since SSH user enumeration often doesn't reliably yield results this way, I will try a different approach.

Next, I will try a direct SSH login attempt with a common username such as "root" or "admin" and a small password list from rockyou.txt to attempt password guessing on that user.

I will start with the user "root" and try the first 50 passwords from rockyou.txt for a quick test.

Command:
head -n 50 /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt > rockyou_50.txt
hydra -L root -P rockyou_50.txt -s 22022 ssh://172.10.0.3 -t 4 -o hydra_ssh_crack.txt -q

This will attempt to crack SSH password for root using 50 common passwords.
